.\" termin.al-name: logout
.\" termin.al-usage: logout
.\" termin.al-summary: End the authenticated session.
.TH LOGOUT 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
logout \- End the authenticated session.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
logout
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Identifies the session-ending command name, but authentication is unavailable in the current browser demo. There is no authenticated session for logout to end.
.SH FAILURES
Every invocation returns the stable command-rejected diagnostic:
.PP
Authentication is unavailable until the host authentication work is implemented.
.PP
Arguments do not change this outcome.
.SH NOTES
No shell, pane, theme preference, cookie, token or browser-storage value is cleared.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ logout
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
login(1), whoami(1)
